According to the LoRaWAN specs, the PHY layer payload includes the MAC Header (MHDR = 1B long), the MAC payload and the Message Integrity Code (MIC = 4B long). When the maximum useful payload is considered, the overall time-on-air ranges from TOA ≈ 0.2 s (when SF = 7, B = 250 kHz, O = 0 and CR=4/5 is used) to TOA ≈ 4.0 s (when SF = 12, B = 125 kHz, O = 1 and CR=4/8 is used).

